orming ring forms around the bar, which alters the\nmetallicity of the inner regions of the galaxy. Further out in the disc,\nbar-induced resonances lead to metal-rich ridges in the $V_{\\phi}-r$ plane --\nthe longest of which is due to the Outer Lindblad Resonance. Our results\nsuggest the Milky Way has an uncommonly quiet merger history, which leads to an\nessentially in-situ bulge, and highlight the significant effects the bar can\nhave on the surrounding disc.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 15 Nov 2019 19:00:05 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 20 Nov 2019 14:50:40 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Mon, 20 Apr 2020 14:45:08 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-05-06"}
